<paragraph id="8B8336DDD362FFC5FF47FCC1DB6DFC16" blockId="1.[151,1437,786,992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="482">
Species of the genus can be recognized by the following characters: the gray ground color of forewing with a dark medial band, one or several dark discal spots, and subbasal and postdiscal series of dark spots. The forewing vein R4 and R5 are stalked for 1/2 length of R4; the R3 and R4+5 are stalked about 1/4 length of R3 (
<figureCitation id="13072A58D362FFC5FB64FC89DAA0FC82" box="[1204,1263,858,884]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,2004,2028]" captionTargetId="figure-292@1.[315,1273,995,1988]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Wing venation of Stictane fractilinea (female, INU˗10364T) from Thailand." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6574336" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6574336/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="482">Fig 1</figureCitation>
); the hindwing veins Rs and M1 are stalked for the half length of M1, from the upper part of the discal cell (
<figureCitation id="13072A58D362FFC5FB15FCADDB4EFC6E" box="[1221,1281,894,920]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,2004,2028]" captionTargetId="figure-292@1.[315,1273,995,1988]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Wing venation of Stictane fractilinea (female, INU˗10364T) from Thailand." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6574336" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6574336/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="482">Fig 1</figureCitation>
). In the male genitalia, the uncus is slender and long or short; the valva is narrow, with a saccular process; and the aedeagus vesica bears cornuti. In the female genitalia, the corpus bursae is scobinate, with long spines (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B2CD362FFC5FBB2FC15DB5AFC16" author="Holloway, J. D." box="[1122,1301,966,992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="482" pagination="279 - 486" refId="ref6724" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The Moths of Borneo: Family Arctiidae, Subfamily Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, 7, 279 - 486." type="journal article" year="2001">Holloway 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
